Protests erupted on Monday after an eight-year-old girl drowned while fetching water. QWAQWA - A ministerial delegation is expected to visit a volatile QwaQwa in the eastern Free State.
Protests erupted on Monday after an eight-year-old girl drowned while fetching water. READ: ANC wants trustworthy Free State government The area has had water shortages for years. Residents barricaded roads and some reports say doctors and nurses were trapped inside the local hospital. READ: Taps are dry in Qwaqwa Many parts of the town have reportedly been locked down. People are gathering again outside the municipal buildings. Maluti-A-Phofung Municipality was placed under administration two years ago.